Reasoning: The paper deals with consistent query answering and repair checking in the context of databases, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Database). The use of universal constraints and the complexity analysis suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The algorithms and computational complexity analysis also suggest relevance to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
